.TH KALK 1 "2026-03-15" "kalk" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kalk \- a minimal terminal spreadsheet
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kalk
.RI [ file.csv ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kalk
is a minimal VisiCalc-inspired spreadsheet for the terminal.
It reads and writes CSV files and supports formulas, cell formatting,
row/column operations, and title locking.
.PP
The grid supports columns A\-IV (256) and rows 1\-1024.
.SH NAVIGATION
.TP
.B Arrow keys
Move cursor
.TP
.B Tab
Move to next column
.TP
.B Enter
Move to next row
.TP
.B Home
Jump to cell A1 (or first unlocked cell)
.TP
.B >
Go to a specific cell (type reference, e.g. B12)
.SH ENTERING DATA
.PP
Type a number, formula, or label directly. Formulas start with
.BR + ", " \- ", " ( ", or " @ .
Labels can be entered directly or prefixed with
.BR \(dq .
.TP
.B Backspace/Delete
Clear current cell
.TP
.B !
Force recalculation
.SH FORMULAS
.PP
Formulas support arithmetic operators (+, \-, *, /), parentheses, cell
references (e.g. A1, $B$2), and functions:
.TP
.B @SUM(range)
Sum of values in range (e.g. @SUM(A1...A10))
.TP
.B @ABS(expr)
Absolute value
.TP
.B @INT(expr)
Integer part (truncate)
.TP
.B @SQRT(expr)
Square root
.PP
Cell references can use
.B $
to mark absolute columns or rows:
.B $A1
(absolute column),
.B A$1
(absolute row),
.B $A$1
(both).
Absolute references are preserved during replicate operations.
.SH COMMANDS
.PP
Press
.B /
to enter command mode. Available commands:
.TP
.B /B
Blank current cell (clear value, keep format)
.TP
.B /C
Clear entire spreadsheet
.TP
.B /D R\fR,\fB /D C
Delete current row or column
.TP
.B /I R\fR,\fB /I C
Insert row or column at cursor
.TP
.B /F \fIformat\fR
Set cell format: L(eft) R(ight) I(nteger) G(eneral) D(efault) $(dollar) %(percent) *(bar graph)
.TP
.B /GC
Set global column width (4\-20)
.TP
.B /GF \fIformat\fR
Set global default format
.TP
.B /M
Move row or column (use arrow keys to drag, Enter to confirm, Esc to cancel)
.TP
.B /R
Replicate (copy) cells. Select source range, then target location. Formulas
adjust relative references automatically.
.TP
.B /SL
Load CSV file
.TP
.B /SS
Save CSV file
.TP
.B /SQ
Save and quit
.TP
.B /TV\fR,\fB /TH\fR,\fB /TB\fR,\fB /TN
Lock title rows/columns: Vertical, Horizontal, Both, or None
.TP
.B /Q
Quit (prompts if unsaved changes)
.SH FILES
.PP
kalk reads and writes standard CSV files. Formulas are stored as entered
(e.g. +A1+B1) and recalculated on load.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal exit
.TP
.B 1
Error (e.g. failed to load file)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B kalk
Start with an empty spreadsheet
.TP
.B kalk budget.csv
Open an existing CSV file
